{"sectionId":737,"sectionIdLiteral":"737","humanId":"lesson-316","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"All gifts I give my brothers are my own.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 316"},"annotation":"W-316","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-316\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"737#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>As every gift my brothers give is mine, so every gift I give belongs to me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Each one allows a past mistake to go, and leave no shadow on the holy mind my Father loves.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>His grace is given me in every gift a brother has received throughout all time, and past all time as well.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>My treasure house is full, and angels watch its open doors that not one gift is lost, and only more are added.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Let me come to where my treasures are, and enter in where I am truly welcome and at home, among the gifts that God has given me.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"737#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, I would accept Your gifts today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I do not recognize them.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"737#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Yet I trust that You Who gave them will provide the means by which I can behold them, see their worth, and cherish only them as what I want.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"As every gift my brothers give is mine, so every gift I give belongs to me. Each one allows a past mistake to go, and leave no shadow on the holy mind my Father loves. His grace is given me in every","contentType":"acim-conte